---
description: Commit, push, PR workflow
alwaysApply: false
---

When doing commit/push/PR:

- Split changes into logical commits (max 3).
- Write commit messages in Conventional Commits format (as in AGENTS.md). Use consistent scopes based on project modules/areas.
- Prefer configuring commit lint to enforce Conventional Commits format.
- Create a branch with a sensible name (feature/..., fix/..., chore/...).
- Push to remote.
- Create a PR with: Summary (2–3 sentences), Changes (bullet points), Testing (how to test).
- Use git and gh CLI.

When modifying features: update relevant documentation (e.g. /docs), keep README in sync, maintain CHANGELOG if the project uses it (see AGENTS.md).
